sentences: Deborah Ruth Lurie (born March 9, 1974) is an American composer, arranger, and music producer.
In 2015, she received the ASCAP Shirley Walker Award to honor her achievements contributing to the diversity of film and television music.
The Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences extended membership to her in 2016 for her contributions to motion pictures.
